  "rollout_plan_displayname": "Will ship enabled for all users",
  "motivation": "Currently there is no web standard way to control whether text decorations (underlines, overlines, line-throughs) appear over whitespace characters. Authors commonly want to suppress the underline under leading/trailing spaces in inline elements, but CSS provides no mechanism for this. The `text-decoration-skip-spaces` property fills this gap, allowing precise control over decoration rendering around whitespace. This is useful for navigation menus, links, and any text where the decoration should visually attach only to non-space characters.",
